Title: owo fileactions

BodyStart:
usage:
  owo {path to a directory} {action} {filename}

owo fileactions:
  owo -[t]ouch or -[n]ew        | create a new file and open/edit it
  owo -[e]dit                   | edit a file
  owo -[d]elete or -[r]e[m]ove  | delete a file
  owo -dir or -mkdir            | create a directory

owo currently does not support deletion of directories

example: 
  owo actions -e touch
  will open the file /actions/touch in your preferred editor
  
a folder has been included that documents all the fileactions that owo can do
try: owo actions
BodyEnd:

